    "description":  "Humphrey Cadoux-Hudson CBE is Lead Non-Executive Director at the Department for Energy Security and Net Zero ( DESNZ ). He is also Non-Executive Chair of the Nominations and Governance Committee. Until June 2022, Humphrey Cadoux-Hudson, worked for EDF UK, most latterly as Managing Director ( MD ) of its Nuclear Development business. In his 20-year EDF career, he led the team that delivered Hinckley Point C into construction and acted as non-exec Chairman for HPC Generation Company Ltd and Chairman and CEO of Sizewell C Generation Company Ltd. Prior to becoming MD , Humphrey was MD of Nuclear New Build (2009 - 2017) and CFO (2003-2009). Before joining EDF, Humphrey was Executive Director of SEEBOARD Group, formerly Southeastern Electricity Board. His early career was with KPMG from 1984 1991.",
